definition.value: measurement of the level of HVA in themedulla oblongata. HVA, homovanillic acid, is a catecholamine metabolite.

The measurement of norepinephrine level in the medulla oblongata. Norepinephrine is a catecholamine hormone that functions as a neurotransmitter in the sympathetic nervous system. It is also called noradrenaline.

label.value: cervical spinal cord monoamine hormone measurement

definition.value: Measurement of the amount in the cervical spinal cord of an amine compound containing one amino group and derived from an aromatic amino acid, that is produced in one part or organ of the body and initiates or regulates the activity of an organ or a group of cells in another part of the body.
measurement of the level of DOPAC in the cervical spine. DOPAC, the 3-O-methyl ether of (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl)acetic acid, is a catecholamine metabolite.

The measurement of norepinephrine level in the cervical spinal cord . Norepinephrine is a catecholamine hormone that functions as a neurotransmitter in the sympathetic nervous system. It is also called noradrenaline.

Measurement of the amount of any xenobiotic or metabolic kinetics in a specified sample of blood. A xenobiotic is a chemical compound foreign to a given biologic system, or more specifically, a pharmacologically, endocrinologically, or toxicologically active substance not endogenously produced and therefore foreign to an organism.

label.value: elimination half-life of nifedipine in the plasma

value.value: The time it takes for the body to eliminate or breakdown half of a dose of this potent vasodilator agent, in practice the time taken for plasma concentration of nifedipine to be reduced by 50%.
This is a measure of the content of this potent vasodilator agent in blood plasma.

label.value: plasma nifedipine level area under curve

value.value: A calculated measurement in which a series of measurements of the amount of nifedipine in a specified volume of plasma is plotted against time for a single individual and the extent of the two dimensional region bounded by the curve and the axes of the graph is determined.

definition.value: The mean residence time is the average time a dose of nifedipine remains in the blood.

value.value: The measurement of the rate at which nifedipine is eliminated from blood plasma.

label.value: volume of distribution of nifedipine in the blood

value.value: In pharmacology, the volume of distribution (VD, also known as apparent volume of distribution) is the theoretical volume that would be necessary to contain the total amount of an administered drug at the same concentration that it is observed in the blood plasma. It is defined as the distribution of a medication between plasma and the rest of the body after oral or parenteral dosing.

label.value: lung weight to tibia length ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of one or both lungs is divided by the length of tibia, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to tibia length.

label.value: single kidney weight to tibia length ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of one kidney is divided by the length of tibia, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to tibia length.

label.value: nasal septum epithelium intracellular mucus area to basement membrane width ratio

value.value: The amount of stored mucosubstance in the epithelium of nasal septum quantified by the area of AB-PAS (alcian blue periodic acid Schiff) positive tissue per unit width of basement membrane.

definition.value: measurement related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the tube descending from the larynx and branching into the right and left main bronchi.

value.value: the measurement of the the enclosing boundary of the trachea lined by the apical surface of epithelium
The measurement of total cartilage area in the tracheal ring.

label.value: trachea cartilage area to trachea lumen circumference ratio

definition.value: Measurement which has been normalized or adjusted by a mathematical process or computation of any measurement related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the tube descending from the larynx and branching into the right and left main bronchi.

value.value: Maximal cartilage thickness was is determined by measuring the perpendicular distance between outer boundaries of cartilage rings.
measurement of the distance between the basement membrane (on the serosal surface) and the apical membrane lumenally
Submucosal gland area determined by measuring the total area of both serous and mucus components of the gland structures via histology

label.value: trachea submucosal gland area to trachea lumenal circumference ratio
trachea submucosal gland intracellular mucus area

value.value: This is determined by histological measurement of the intracellular mucus area in the submucosal gland of the trachea.

label.value: trachea submucosal gland intracellular mucus area to total trachea submucosal gland area ratio

value.value: A calculated value in which the cross sectional area of the submucosal gland taken up by mucus is divided by the total cross-sectional area of the submucosal gland, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to trachea submucosal gland area.

The proportion, quantity, or volume of C-reactive protein (CRP) found in the blood. CRP is an acute phase reactant protein used to indicate inflammatory illness. It is believed to be of value in predicting coronary events.

The proportion, quantity, or volume of C-reactive protein (CRP) found in the serum, the clear liquid that is separated from blood after it has clotted completely, i.e. blood plasma from which fibrinogen has been removed. CRP is an acute phase reactant protein used to indicate inflammatory illness. It is believed to be of value in predicting coronary events.

The proportion, quantity, or volume of C-reactive protein (CRP) found in the plasma, the fibrinogen-containing fluid portion of the blood in which the particulate components are suspended. CRP is an acute phase reactant protein used to indicate inflammatory illness. It is believed to be of value in predicting coronary events.

label.value: kidney total CD3 positive T cell count

definition.value: The number of CD3-positive T cells in the kidney.
Any quantitation of the cells and/or cell types which constitute the make-up of the kidney

label.value: kidney total  CD45 positive leukocyte count
blood regulatory T cell count to total T cell count ratio

definition.value: Measurement of the relative abundance of regulatory T cells whose function is control or suppression of the T cell mediated immune response. Regulatory T cells are generally distinguished from other classes of lymphocytes on the basis of the presence and/or absence of a number of specific cell surface marker proteins.

label.value: spleen regulatory T cell count to total T cell count ratio

definition.value: Measurement of the relative abundance of regulatory T cells in the spleen. Regulatory T cells control or suppress T cell mediated immune response. Regulatory T cells are generally distinguished from other classes of lymphocytes on the basis of the presence and/or absence of a number of specific cell surface marker proteins.

A measurement which has been normalized or adjusted by a mathematical process or computation of the brain infarction volume. A brain infarction is an area of necrotic tissue in the brain resulting from a reduction or obstruction of the oxygen or blood supply to the brain.

label.value: cerebrum infarct volume to total cerebrum volume ratio

definition.value: A calculated value in which the volume of cerebrum infarction is divided by the total volume of the cerebrum, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction or percentage, thus normalizing it to the size of the brain.

label.value: verapamil apparent influx permeability clearance in brain

value.value: This is a calculated measurement which is used to determine passive permeability coefficients. It helps assess the rate of verapamil permeation and the presence of active transport processes in a two compartment system involving brain and blood plasma. This calculated value is determined by this formula: Capp(t)/Cp(t) = Kin,tissue x AUC(t)/Cp(t) + Vi, where Capp=apparent concentration, p=plasma, and Vi=rapidly equilibrated distribution volume of verapamil in brain.

label.value: verapamil apparent influx permeability clearance in retina

value.value: This is a calculated measurement which is used to determine passive permeability coefficients. It helps assess the rate of verapamil permeation and the presence of active transport processes in a two compartment system involving retina and blood plasma. This calculated value is determined by this formula: Capp(t)/Cp(t) = Kin,tissue x AUC(t)/Cp(t) + Vi, where Capp=apparent concentration, p=plasma, and Vi=rapidly equilibrated distribution volume of verapamil in retina.

label.value: verapamil apparent influx permeability clearance in aqueous humor

value.value: This is a calculated measurement which is used to determine passive permeability coefficients. It helps assess the rate of verapamil permeation and the presence of active transport processes in a two compartment system involving aqueous humor and blood plasma. This calculated value is determined by this formula: Capp(t)/Cp(t) = Kin,tissue x AUC(t)/Cp(t) + Vi, where Capp=apparent concentration, p=plasma, and Vi=rapidly equilibrated distribution volume of verapamil in the aqueous humor.
